Y2  - 2026/05/04/19:56:08
AB  - Promoting climate-smart agricultural practices improves smallholder farmers’ knowledge and farming practices in low- and middle-income countries (LMICs), but it is limited in scope and methodological rigor. Interventions promoting climate-smart agriculture (CSA) approaches, such as farmer field schools and agriculture extension services, show improvements in knowledge gains and adoption of these practices by smallholder farmers in LMICs. However, due to methodological limitations, confidence in study findings is low.
